Chelsea’s squad to face Crystal Palace in today’s Premier League tie has been revealed. According to Football London, Chelsea manager, Thomas Tuchel, has named a 24-man squad to tackle Crystal Palace at the Selhurst Park Stadium. Tuchel’s men head to the game following a 2-0 victory over Porto in the Champions League quarter-final first-leg encounter on Wednesday. Chelsea are presently in the fifth position on the Premier League table with 51 points from 30 games. Chelsea’s full squad against Crystal Palace: Goalkeepers: Edouard Mendy, Kepa Arrizabalaga, Willy Caballero and Karlo Ziger. Defenders: Reece James, Cesar Azpilicueta, Antonio Rudiger, Kurt Zouma, Andreas Christensen, Ben Chilwell, Marcos Alonso and Emerson Palmieri. Midfielders: Christian Pulisic, Hakim Ziyech, Callum Hudson-Odoi, Jorginho, N’Golo Kante, Mateo Kovacic, Billy Gilmour, Mason Mount, and Kai Havertz. Strikers: Tammy Abraham, Timo Werner and Olivier Giroud. The kick-off time for Chelsea vs Crystal Palace is 5.30 pm.